{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> Ἄρειος</b> [ᾰ], ον, <br /> also α, ον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 413 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Ionic dialect</i> Ἀρήϊος, η, ο; <i>Aeolic dialect</i> Ἀρεύϊος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus “Supp.” 1a.10\">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]: (Ἄρης):— <b>devoted to Ares, warlike, martial</b>; in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], mostly of warriors, Μενέλαος Ἀρήιος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 3.339, +others; Ἀρήϊοι υἷες Ἀχαιῶν 11.800, +others \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of arms, Ἀρήϊα τεύχεα δύω[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6.340, compare 10.407\">Refs</a>]; the <i>Attic dialect</i> form only in the phrase τεῖχος Ἄρειον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4.407, +others; also in 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus, ἀρήιοι ἀγῶνες\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] conflicts <b>in real war,</b> opposed to γυμνικοί,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 9.33; ὅπλον ἀ. 4.23 \">Refs</a>]; of a man, as <i>substantive</i>, <b>warrior,</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6.98; Ἀθηνᾶ Ἀρεία “OGI” 229.70 (from Smyrna), compare “IG” 12(5).913 (from Tenos): _comparative_ ἀρειότερος (which see) 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 548 is probably to be read instead of med from ἀρείων, as χερειότερος from χερείων. \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> Ἄρειος (also Ἄρεος, Ἄρηος), ὁ (i.e. μήν), name of month in Thessaly, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “GDI” 1449, etc. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> Ἄρειον πεδίον, = <b>Campus Martius,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 7.59, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pompeius” 53\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>] (also name of a plain in Thrace, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 13.10.7)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; τῶν τελῶν τὸ καλούμενον Ἄρειον, = <b>legio Martia,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Appianus Historicus “Bella Civilia” 3.45\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; Ἄρεια, τά, = <b>ludi Martiales,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 56.46. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> Ἄρειον, τό, ={ξιφίον}, Ps.-[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 4.20\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; ={ἰσάτις}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.184. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> ={Ἄριος, Μάγοι καὶ πᾶν τὸ Ἄρειον γένος} [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.AD: Damascius Philosophus “de Principiis” 125.\">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>] <br /><Level1><b>__A</b></Level1><b> Ἄρειος πάγος</b> [πᾰ], ὁ, <b>the hill of Ares,</b> at Athens, Ἀρήϊος π.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.52, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 685, 690, etc.; ἡ βουλὴ ἡ ἐξ Ἀρείου πάγου “IG” 1.38a (probably), 2.476.59, +others, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.133, compare 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 26.12, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ἀθηναίων Πολιτεία” 4.4; ἡ ἐν Ἀ. πάγῳ βουλή 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 20.157, 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.81, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1273b39; βουλή Ἀρεία “IG” 3.824\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; εἰς τὸν Ἄ. πάγον ἀναβῆναι become a member of the court, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 7.37, 12.154; ἐν Ἀ. πάγῳ δοῦναι δίκην 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1398b26; ψευδομαρτύρια τὰ ἐξ Ἀ. πάγου [prev. author] “Ath.” 59.6.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]—The <i>compound</i> Ἀρειόπᾰγος only in a late <i>Attic dialect</i> Inscription, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 3.1005\">Refs</a>]; but we find the noun Ἀρεοπᾰγίτης (Ἀρευ- [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work]2.839.7) [ῑ], \">Refs</a>] ου, ὁ, <b>Areopagite,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.81, “IG” 3.746, compare 635, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ἀθηναίων Πολιτεία” 3.6, etc.: proverbial, Ἀρεοπαγίτου σιωπηλότερος\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] 'as silent as the grave', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Themistius Sophista “Orationes” 21.263a; στεγανώτερος 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 1.13\">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]:—<i>adjective</i> Ἀρεοπᾰγῖτις, βουλή[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ἀθηναίων Πολιτεία” 41.2, 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 2.3\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; Ἀρεοπᾰγῑτικός, ή, όν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 7 at Title Page, 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 6.1.8.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0698","accentedUnicode":"Ἀρεοπαγίτης","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0697","matchingForm":"Ἄρειος Πάγος","stepTransliteration":"areios pagos","gloss":"Areopagus","_searchResultRange":"Acts.17.19-22@Acts.17.19-34","_zh_tw_Gloss":"亞略巴古","_es_Gloss":"Areópago","_zh_Gloss":"亚略巴古"},{"strongNumber":"G0698","matchingForm":"Ἀρεοπαγίτης","stepTransliteration":"areopagitēs","gloss":"Areopagite","_searchResultRange":"Acts.17.34@Acts.17.19-34","_zh_tw_Gloss":"亞略巴古的官","_es_Gloss":"areopagita","_zh_Gloss":"亚略巴古的官"}],"shortDef":"member of the Areopagus","mediumDef":" <BR> § member of the Areopagus <br /><b>a judge of the court of Areopagus,</b> <ref='Act.17.34'>Acts 17:34</ref>*","stepGloss":"Areopagite","stepTransliteration":"areopagitēs","count":1,"_es_Definition":"areopagita (miembro de la corte de Areópago)","_zh_tw_Definition":"亞略巴古法庭的一位成員 (徒 17:34)","_zh_Definition":"亚略巴古法庭的一位成员 (徒 17:34)","_step_Type":"place","_step_Link":"37.98333333333333,23.73333333333333","_stepDetailLexicalTag":"[[\"named\",\"G0697\",\"Areopagus\",4,\"Ἄρειος Πάγος\"],[\"of a group\",\"G0698\",\"Areopagite\",1,\"Ἀρεοπαγίτης\"]]","_vi_Definition":"A-rê-ô-ba hoặc A-rê-ô-pa-gu; 